instructions.name: c.jal
instructions.description: C.JAL an RV32C-only instruction that performs the same operation as C.

instructions.name: c.flw
instructions.description: C.FLW an RV32FC-only instruction that loads a single-precision floating-point value from memory into floating-point register rd′.

instructions.name: c.fsw
instructions.description: C.FSW an RV32FC-only instruction that stores a single-precision floating-point value in floating-point register rs2′ to memory.

instructions.name: c.fswsp
instructions.description: C.FSWSP an RV32FC-only instruction that stores a single-precision floating-point value in floating-point register rs2 to memory.

instructions.name: fmvp.d.x
instructions.description: FMVP.D.X encoded in the OP-FP major opcode with funct3=0 and funct7=1011001.

instructions.name: slli
instructions.description: SLLI is a logical left shift (zeros are shifted into the lower bits);

instructions.name: srli
instructions.description: SRLI is a logical right shift (zeros are shifted into the upper bits);

instructions.name: srai
instructions.description: SRAI is an arithmetic right shift (the original sign bit is copied into the vacated upper bits).

instructions.name: rdcycleh
instructions.description: RDCYCLEH only present when XLEN=32 and reads bits 63-32 of the same cycle counter.

instructions.name: rdtimeh
instructions.description: RDTIMEH only present when XLEN=32 and reads bits 63-32 of the same real-time counter.

instructions.name: rdinstreth
instructions.description: RDINSTRETH only present when XLEN=32 and reads bits 63-32 of the same instruction counter.

instructions.name: ld
instructions.description: The LD instruction loads a 64-bit value from memory into register rd for RV64I.

instructions.name: c.ld
instructions.description: C.LD an RV64C-only instruction that loads a 64-bit value from memory into register rd′.

instructions.name: c.sd
instructions.description: C.SD an RV64C-only instruction that stores a 64-bit value in register rs2′ to memory.

instructions.name: c.addiw
instructions.description: C.ADDIW an RV64C-only instruction that performs the same computation but produces a 32-bit result, then sign-extends result to 64 bits.

instructions.name: c.srai
instructions.description: C.SRAI defined analogously to C.

instructions.name: c.subw
instructions.description: C.SUBW an RV64C-only instruction that subtracts the value in register rs2′ from the value in register rd′, then sign-extends the lower 32 bits of the difference before writing the result to register rd′.

instructions.name: c.addw
instructions.description: C.ADDW an RV64C-only instruction that adds the values in registers rd′ and rs2′, then sign-extends the lower 32 bits of the sum before writing the result to register rd′.

instructions.name: c.ldsp
instructions.description: C.LDSP valid only when rd≠x0; the code points with rd=x0 are reserved.

instructions.name: c.sdsp
instructions.description: C.SDSP an RV64C-only instruction that stores a 64-bit value in register rs2 to memory.

instructions.name: lwu
instructions.description: The LWU instruction, on the other hand, zero-extends the 32-bit value from memory for RV64I.

instructions.name: addiw
instructions.description: ADDIW is an RV64I instruction that adds the sign-extended 12-bit immediate to register rs1 and produces the proper sign extension of a 32-bit result in rd.

instructions.name: mulw
instructions.description: MULW is an RV64 instruction that multiplies the lower 32 bits of the source registers, placing the sign extension of the lower 32 bits of the result into the destination register.

instructions.name: fmvp.q.x
instructions.description: FMVP.Q.X encoded in the OP-FP major opcode with funct3=0 and funct7=1011011.

instructions.name: lr.w
instructions.description: LR.W a word from the address in rs1, places the sign-extended value in rd, and registers a reservation set—a set of bytes that subsumes the bytes in the addressed word.

instructions.name: c.lw
instructions.description: C.LW a 32-bit value from memory into register rd′.

instructions.name: c.sw
instructions.description: C.SW a 32-bit value in register rs2′ to memory.

instructions.name: c.addi16sp
instructions.description: C.ADDI16SP the non-zero sign-extended 6-bit immediate to the value in the stack pointer (sp=x2), where the immediate is scaled to represent multiples of 16 in the range [-512, 496].

instructions.name: c.lui
instructions.description: C.LUI the non-zero 6-bit immediate field into bits 17–12 of the destination register, clears the bottom 12 bits, and sign-extends bit 17 into all higher bits of the destination.

instructions.name: c.sub
instructions.description: C.SUB the value in register rs2′ from the value in register rd′, then writes the result to register rd′.

instructions.name: c.xor
instructions.description: C.XOR the bitwise XOR of the values in registers rd′ and rs2′, then writes the result to register rd′.

instructions.name: c.or
instructions.description: C.OR the bitwise OR of the values in registers rd′ and rs2′, then writes the result to register rd′.

instructions.name: c.and
instructions.description: C.AND the bitwise AND of the values in registers rd′ and rs2′, then writes the result to register rd′.

instructions.name: c.j
instructions.description: C.J an unconditional control transfer.

instructions.name: c.beqz
instructions.description: C.BEQZ conditional control transfers.

instructions.name: c.bnez
instructions.description: C.BNEZ defined analogously, but it takes the branch if rs1′ contains a nonzero value.

instructions.name: c.lwsp
instructions.description: C.LWSP a 32-bit value from memory into register rd.

instructions.name: c.jr
instructions.description: C.JR valid only when rs1≠x0; the code point with rs1=x0 is reserved.

instructions.name: c.mv
instructions.description: C.MV valid only when rs2≠x0; the code points with rs2=x0 correspond to the C.

instructions.name: c.jalr
instructions.description: C.JALR valid only when rs1≠x0; the code point with rs1=x0 corresponds to the C.

instructions.name: c.add
instructions.description: C.ADD only valid when rs2≠x0; the code points with rs2=x0 correspond to the C.

instructions.name: c.swsp
instructions.description: C.SWSP a 32-bit value in register rs2 to memory.

instructions.name: c.fld
instructions.description: C.FLD an RV32DC/RV64DC-only instruction that loads a double-precision floating-point value from memory into floating-point register rd′.

instructions.name: c.fsd
instructions.description: C.FSD an RV32DC/RV64DC-only instruction that stores a double-precision floating-point value in floating-point register rs2′ to memory.

instructions.name: c.fldsp
instructions.description: C.FLDSP an RV32DC/RV64DC-only instruction that loads a double-precision floating-point value from memory into floating-point register rd.

instructions.name: c.fsdsp
instructions.description: C.FSDSP an RV32DC/RV64DC-only instruction that stores a double-precision floating-point value in floating-point register rs2 to memory.

instructions.name: fsd
instructions.description: FSD a double-precision value from the floating-point registers to memory.

instructions.name: fli.d
instructions.description: FLI.D encoded like FLI.

instructions.name: flw
instructions.description: FLW a single-precision floating-point value from memory into floating-point register rd.

instructions.name: fmadd.s
instructions.description: FMADD.S the values in rs1 and rs2, adds the value in rs3, and writes the final result to rd.

instructions.name: fmsub.s
instructions.description: FMSUB.S the values in rs1 and rs2, subtracts the value in rs3, and writes the final result to rd.

instructions.name: fnmsub.s
instructions.description: FNMSUB.S the values in rs1 and rs2, negates the product, adds the value in rs3, and writes the final result to rd.

instructions.name: fnmadd.s
instructions.description: FNMADD.S the values in rs1 and rs2, negates the product, subtracts the value in rs3, and writes the final result to rd.

instructions.name: fsub.s
instructions.description: FSUB.S the single-precision floating-point subtraction of rs2 from rs1.

instructions.name: fsqrt.s
instructions.description: FSQRT.S the square root of rs1.

instructions.name: feq.s
instructions.description: FEQ.S a quiet comparison: it only sets the invalid operation exception flag if either input is a signaling NaN.

instructions.name: frrm
instructions.description: FRRM the Rounding Mode field frm (fcsr bits 7--5) and copies it into the least-significant three bits of integer register rd, with zero in all other bits.

instructions.name: frcsr
instructions.description: FRCSR fcsr by copying it into integer register rd.

instructions.name: fli.s
instructions.description: FLI.S encoded like FMV.

instructions.name: fround.s
instructions.description: FROUND.S encoded like FCVT.

instructions.name: froundnx.s
instructions.description: FROUNDNX.S defined similarly, but it also sets the inexact exception flag if the input differs from the rounded result and is not NaN.

instructions.name: hfence.vvma
instructions.description: HFENCE.VVMA valid only in M-mode or HS-mode.

instructions.name: hfence.gvma
instructions.description: HFENCE.GVMA valid only in HS-mode when mstatus.

instructions.name: lui
instructions.description: LUI places the 32-bit U-immediate value into the destination register rd, filling in the lowest 12 bits with zeros. LUI places the 32-bit U-immediate into register rd, filling in the lowest 12 bits with zeros. The 32-bit result is sign-extended to 64 bits.

instructions.name: auipc
instructions.description: AUIPC forms a 32-bit offset from the U-immediate, filling in the lowest 12 bits with zeros, adds this offset to the address of the AUIPC instruction, then places the result in register rd. AUIPC forms a 32-bit offset from the U-immediate, filling in the lowest 12 bits with zeros, sign-extends the result to 64 bits, adds it to the address of the AUIPC instruction, then places the result in register rd.

instructions.name: jal
instructions.description: JAL stores the address of the instruction following the jump ('pc'+4) into register rd.

instructions.name: jalr
instructions.description: The address of the instruction following the jump (pc+4) is written to register rd.

instructions.name: lh
instructions.description: LH loads a 16-bit value from memory, then sign-extends to 32-bits before storing in rd.

instructions.name: lw
instructions.description: The LW instruction loads a 32-bit value from memory into rd. The LW instruction loads a 32-bit value from memory and sign-extends this to 64 bits before storing it in register rd for RV64I.

instructions.name: lhu
instructions.description: LHU loads a 16-bit value from memory but then zero extends to 32-bits before storing in rd.

instructions.name: addi
instructions.description: ADDI adds the sign-extended 12-bit immediate to register rs1.

instructions.name: sltiu
instructions.description: SLTIU similar but compares the values as unsigned numbers (i.

instructions.name: add
instructions.description: ADD performs the addition of rs1 and rs2.

instructions.name: sub
instructions.description: SUB performs the subtraction of rs2 from rs1.

instructions.name: fence
instructions.description: A FENCE (with fm=0000) orders all memory operations in its predecessor set before all memory operations in its successor set.

instructions.name: pause
instructions.description: PAUSE more appropriate when polling for non-memory events, when polling for multiple events, or when software does not know precisely what events it is polling for.

instructions.name: ecall
instructions.description: The ECALL instruction is used to make a service request to the execution environment.

instructions.name: ebreak
instructions.description: The EBREAK instruction is used to return control to a debugging environment.

instructions.name: nop
instructions.description: NOP encoded as ADDI x0, x0, 0.

instructions.name: mul
instructions.description: MUL performs an XLEN-bit×XLEN-bit multiplication of rs1 by rs2 and places the lower XLEN bits in the destination register.

instructions.name: fli.q
instructions.description: FLI.Q encoded like FLI.

instructions.name: sfence.vma
instructions.description: SFENCE.VMA also used to invalidate entries in the address-translation cache associated with a hart (see ).

instructions.name: sret
instructions.description: SRET used to return from a trap taken into HS-mode or VS-mode.

instructions.name: sctrclr
instructions.description: SCTRCLR the following operations: Zeroes all CTR , for all DEPTH values Zeroes the CTR cycle counter and CCV (see ) Any read of ctrsource, ctrtarget, or ctrdata that follows SCTRCLR, such that it precedes the next qualified control transfer, will return the value 0.

instructions.name: mret
instructions.description: MRET always provided.

instructions.name: wfi
instructions.description: WFI available in all privileged modes, and optionally available to U-mode.

instructions.name: vfmerge.vfm
instructions.description: vfmerge.vfm encoded as a masked instruction (vm=0).

instructions.name: vwredsum.vs
instructions.description: vwredsum.vs the SEW-wide vector elements before summing them.

instructions.name: vfirst.m
instructions.description: vfirst.m x[rd] even if vl=0 (with the value -1, since no mask elements are active).

instructions.name: andn
instructions.description: andn also useful for constant time word-select in systems without the ternary Bitmanip cmov instruction.

instructions.name: fli.h
instructions.description: FLI.H encoded like FLI.

instructions.name: lpad
instructions.description: LPAD encoded with a 20-bit immediate value called the landing-pad-label (LPL) that is matched to the expected landing pad label.

instructions.name: csrrw
instructions.description: CSRRW the old value of the CSR, zero-extends the value to XLEN bits, then writes it to integer register rd.

csrs.name: vstart
csrs.description: The vstart register defined to have only enough writable bits to hold the largest element index (one less than the maximum VLMAX).

csrs.name: seed
csrs.description: seed is an unprivileged CSR located at address 0x015. The 32-bit contents of seed are as follows:

csrs.name: jvt
csrs.description: Table jump base vector and control register

csrs.name: time
csrs.description: The time register a read-only shadow of the memory-mapped mtime register.

csrs.name: vl
csrs.description: The vl register an unsigned integer specifying the number of elements to be updated with results from a vector instruction, as further detailed in .

csrs.name: sstatus
csrs.description: The sstatus register a subset of the mstatus register.

csrs.name: hstatus
csrs.description: The hstatus register facilities analogous to the mstatus register for tracking and controlling the exception behavior of a VS-mode guest.

csrs.name: hgeie
csrs.description: The hgeie register an HSXLEN-bit read/write register, formatted as shown in , that contains enable bits for the guest external interrupts at this hart.

csrs.name: hgatp
csrs.description: The hgatp register considered active for the purposes of the address-translation algorithm unless the effective privilege mode is U and hstatus.

csrs.name: mstatus
csrs.description: The mstatus register a superset of the HS-level sstatus register but is not a superset of vsstatus.

csrs.name: misa
csrs.description: The misa register reset to enable the maximal set of supported extensions, as described in .

csrs.name: mideleg
csrs.description: The mideleg register the delegation of this interrupt to S-mode versus M-mode.

csrs.name: mepc
csrs.description: The mepc register written with the virtual address of the instruction that was interrupted, and mcause is set to a value indicating the source of the NMI.

csrs.name: mcause
csrs.description: The mcause register set to a value indicating the cause of the reset.

csrs.name: mtval2
csrs.description: The mtval2 register then set to what would be otherwise written into the mcause register by the unexpected trap.
